If you want to create an artist model instance when a user is created/registered. Consider, &quot;Extending the Django User Model&quot;. You can do this using a One to One relationship or by using a Proxy User model.

An example of the One To One Model:

    class Artist(models.Model):
        user = models.OneToOneField(User, on_delete=models.CASCADE)
        # Your artist fields

Then you can add some signals to update the artist model on user registration/changes.

    @receiver(post_save, sender=User)
    def create_user_artist(sender, instance, created, **kwargs):
        if created:
            Artist.objects.create(user=instance)
    
    @receiver(post_save, sender=User)
    def save_user_artist(sender, instance, **kwargs):
        instance.artist.save()

By doing this, if the user is created or updated the relevant signal will be called, updating the artist model instance.

